    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-12-29T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-12-29T06:00:00-05:00" n="666"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d666">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.504/363: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dickerson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Kuibyshev</hi> (<hi rend="smallcaps"
                            >Moscow</hi>)</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1941-12-29T14:00:00+03:00">December 29, 1941—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 9:25 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2109. With reference to the decree of June 26, 1940,<note n="40"
                        xml:id="d666fn40">See telegram No. 760, June 27, 1940, from the Chargé in
                        the Soviet Union, <ref target="frus1940v03#pg_202">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1940, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">iii</hi>, p. 202</ref>.</note> forbidding all
                    workers in Soviet factories and enterprises to leave their employment without
                    permission, under penalty of imprisonment of from 2 to 4 months, the local press
                    has published a decree dated December 26, 1941, raising the penalty for
                    “arbitrary departure” of workers in armaments <pb facs="0679" n="667"
                        xml:id="pg_667"/> and related industries to from 5 to 8 years and giving
                    jurisdiction in such cases to court martial. The present decree applies not only
                    to ordinary factories but also to those which have been evacuated. Thus workers
                    in armament plants evacuated to the east are obliged to move with the plant to
                    its new location.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dickerson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
